Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.39,0:22:42.67,sign_32569_308_The_Beast_and_th,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(884,1)}The Beast and the Prince
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.17,0:22:50.01,sign_32675_309_Missing,,0000,0000,0000,,In the deepest, darkest part\Nof a forest lived a tribe,\Nhidden from all. They had \Nlarge wings on their backs\Nand were beautiful, but they were \Nwhat would be called beasts.\N Among them was their princess, \Nwho had huge, ashen wings.\NTheir law said that once one \Nturned sixteen, they would be \Nallowed to fly outside the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.51,0:22:57.48,sign_32865_310_Missing_1,,0000,0000,0000,,And on her sixteenth birthday,\Nthe princess took flight to\Nthe world beyond the forest.\NShe crossed the steep mountains\Nand the surging rivers\Nand reached a land of humans.\NThe moon shone brightly\Nin the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.51,0:22:57.48,sign_32884_311_Missing_2,,0000,0000,0000,,She landed in a castle garden,\Nwhere she found a young man\Ngazing up at the moon.\NThe princess hid in the bushes\Nand stared at the young man,\Nand for the first time,\Nlove bloomed in her heart.\NBut he was clearly of a different race.\NA beast and a human\Ncould never be together.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.98,0:23:04.90,sign_33049_312_Missing_1,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, the princess went to see\Na witch who lived in the same forest\Nand said, "I want to live as a human. \NI want to be united with him."\NThe witch replied like so:\N"I can help you if you offer me\Nyour wings. But keep this in mind.\NNo matter how you disguise yourself,\Nyou are a beast, and you will consume\Nthe prince's life one day."\N\N\NThe princess ripped off her wings\Nand was assaulted by pain\Nfar more intense than she had ever felt.\NShe could never fly again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.98,0:23:04.90,sign_33049_313_Missing_2,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, she smiled happily,\Nwith tears of joy\Nstreaming down her face.\N"I'm human! I'm human!\NI'm the same as him now!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.40,0:23:12.37,sign_33205_314_Missing,,0000,0000,0000,,The princess once again set out for the land of humans,\Nthis time on foot. In the desert, she spotted a group of people.\N"Oh, no! Is there anyone who can save him?!" There lay a young man,\Nhis leg bitten by a snake. The princess rushed to his side\Nand sucked the venom out from his wound."Thank you, o brave lady.\NI am the prince of these lands." It was the same young man\Nshe had met in the castle. "I owe my life to you.\NPlease marry me."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.83,0:23:19.75,sign_33419_315_Missing_1,,0000,0000,0000,,A wedding ceremony was held soon after.\NThe priest asked the princess,\Nclad in a wedding dress of pure white,\N"Do you vow to be true to him\Nin good times and in bad,\Nin sickness and in health, \Nuntil death do you part?"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.83,0:23:19.75,sign_33383_316_Missing_2,,0000,0000,0000,,"I do."\NThe two exchanged rings,\Nand when the priest said so,\Nthey sealed their vows with a kiss.\NAnd cheers rang out across the land.\N"Bless the brave girl who \Nsaved our prince's life!"\NThe whole kingdom celebrated\Ntheir marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.21,0:23:27.17,sign_33596_317_Missing,,0000,0000,0000,,"Humans! Humans! They have\Nneither the wings to fly nor the\Nclaws or fangs to hunt. Such weak\Nand frail creatures, but they are\Nso, so warm. Humans are wonderful!"\N\NAfter the wedding, she lived happily\Nas the princess of a human land.\NShe supported the prince in his work,\Ntraveled the world, and saw\Noceans studded with glints of sapphire,\Nsparkling grasslands, and auroras\Nthat swayed like raging flames.\N\NThe princess took the prince's hand\Nand said with a smile on her face,\N"Grab on to me and never let go, *******."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.67,0:23:34.64,sign_33775_318_Missing,,0000,0000,0000,,But the princess's happiness was short-lived.\N\NShe woke up one night to a pain that\Nthreatened to rend her asunder and\Nfound her body turning into one of a beast.\N"Why? I asked you to make me human!"\NOn her back were jet-black wings,\Ntearing through her flesh and skin to spread.\N"Using magic comes at a price.\NYou've attained plenty of happiness as a human.\NNow, it is time for you to lose yourself\Nand turn into an ugly monster,"\Nthe witch of the forest whispered to her.\N"However, if you kill the person you love most,\Nyou will be freed of your curse\Nand return to the beast you originally were."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.10,0:23:42.02,sign_33953_319_Missing,,0000,0000,0000,,The princess gazed at her beloved prince\Nas her claws reached for his throat.\NShe loved him more than anything and anyone,\Nbut the desire to rip his neck apart\Nwelled up inside her.\NAs she desperately tried to\Nclench her fist and stop herself,\Nher claws dug into her skin,\Nand blood started gushing out.\N\N"If I kill the prince, I will be freed of this curse..."\NWith tears streaming down her face,\Nshe kissed the prince on the cheek.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.52,0:23:49.86,sign_34131_320_Missing_1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,1016)}When the prince awoke,\Nthe princess was no longer\Nbeside him. Instead, the bed\Nwas covered in jet-black feathers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.52,0:23:49.86,sign_34131_321_Missing_2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,1016)}In profound sadness,\Nthe prince searched\Nall across the land for her.\NBut nobody had seen the princess.

